==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin '''''vulva''''', earlier ''[[volva]]'' ‘womb, female sexual organ’, probably from ''[[volvare]]'' ‘to turn, wrap around’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈvʌlvə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl2=vulvae}}

# {{anatomy}} The external female [[sexual organs]], collectively.

===Usage note===
"[[vagina]]" is often used to refer to the vulva or female genitals generally, even though strictly speaking the vagina is a specific internal structure.  Calling the vulva the vagina is rather like calling the mouth the throat.

